Text: I know it’s kind of uncomfortable asking questions like this, especially on the spot. What’s been on your mind? Looking for birth control? You can ask me, “Where can I get birth control? How much does it cost?" And even, "How do I talk to a doctor about it?” Heard something crazy about STDs? Ask me, “How do I prevent STDs?" or "Where can I get tested?” Nothing’s off limits here!

Text: STD tests are over 99% accurate and they’re really quick and easy to get done. Usually it involves peeing in a cup, a finger prick, or a vagina swab - and it doesn’t take longer than a few minutes. It’s also super easy to find a place to get tested. If you're worried about it - just get tested ASAP. It's worth it to know!
